HEADWORD: Court-plaster
<hw>Court"-plas`ter</hw> <pr>(k?rt"pl?s`t?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Sticking plaster made by coating taffeta or silk on one side with some adhesive substance, commonly a mixture of isinglass and glycerin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Courtship</ent>⟦br⟧
